The paper deals with image editing using deep neural networks, specifically for faces. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for training, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of warping for semantic edits also involves geometric transformations, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with high-resolution images, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
